  "tour_service.welcome.title": "👋 Welcome to CodeContext AI!",
  "tour_service.welcome.text": "CodeContext AI is a tool for analyzing your codebase. It scans your project, gathers context, and lets you send it to an LLM for analysis, chat, or patch creation.\n\nClick \"Next\" to learn about the features.",
  "tour_service.folders_pr.title": "📂 Folders and GitHub PR",
  "tour_service.folders_pr.text": "Add local folders via the \"Add Folder\" button or clone a GitHub repository by URL.\n\nPull Requests are supported — only PR files will be scanned.",
  "tour_service.filtering.title": "🔧 File Filtering",
  "tour_service.filtering.text": "Configure file extensions, ignore paths, and filtering presets.\n\nEnable Git mode to scan only changed files.",
  "tour_service.compression.title": "⚙️ Compression and Minify",
  "tour_service.compression.text": "Enable Minify to remove extra whitespace, \"No Comments\" to remove comments, and \"No Secrets\" to mask API keys.\n\nSkeleton mode leaves only function stubs.",
  "tour_service.architecture.title": "🌳 Project Architecture",
  "tour_service.architecture.text": "Enable the project tree, dependency graph, and Mermaid diagram to visualize your code architecture.",
  "tour_service.editor_preview.title": "👁 Preview and Diff",
  "tour_service.editor_preview.text": "Use \"Preview\" to see the final prompt. The \"Diff\" tab shows a comparison of original vs processed files.\n\nCopy individual files or everything at once.",
  "tour_service.local_llm.title": "💻 Local LLMs",
  "tour_service.local_llm.text": "Connect local LLMs (Ollama, LM Studio) or cloud APIs (OpenAI).\n\nLLM is used for patch validation and code chat.",
  "tour_service.ai_chat.title": "💬 AI Chat",
  "tour_service.ai_chat.text": "Chat dialog with the LLM that automatically includes the full project context.\n\nAsk questions about the code, request refactoring, or code generation.",
  "tour_service.patcher.title": "🔧 JSON Patcher",
  "tour_service.patcher.text": "Generate a JSON patch via LLM and apply it to project files.\n\nSupported actions: replace, create, delete, append, prepend, insert_before, insert_after.",
  "tour_service.safety_diff.title": "🛡 Safe Diff Review",
  "tour_service.safety_diff.text": "Each patch goes through a diff preview. You can verify changes via LLM.\n\nAccept or reject changes selectively.",
  "tour_service.os_integration.title": "🖥 OS Integration",
  "tour_service.os_integration.text": "Install the context menu (\"CodeContext AI\" on right-click of a folder) and a global CLI.\n\nWindows: via registry. macOS: via Automator. Linux: via .desktop files.",

